ok at this logo and break down what its elements mean.\", \"from\": 481, \"to\": 666, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris 2024 Olympics logo has three features - a flame, a gold medal, and a woman.\", \"from\": 668, \"to\": 753, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 678, \"end\": 691, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"2024 Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The woman sporting a stylish bob haircut in the logo is none other than Marianne, a symbol representing the French Republic.\", \"from\": 755, \"to\": 879, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 827, \"end\": 835, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.351479468610666e-37, \"text\": \"Marianne\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne\"}, {\"begin\": 870, \"end\": 878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic\", \"score\": 0.9058230954090355, \"rank\": 0.1036956542772159, \"text\": \"Republic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She is a symbol of liberty and freedom.\", \"from\": 880, \"to\": 919, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Much like Juan dela Cruz of the Philippines or Uncle Sam of the United States, Marianne holds a significant place in French culture and history.\", \"from\": 921, \"to\": 1065, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 931, \"end\": 945, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Juan_dela_Cruz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1510290065577686e-15, \"text\": \"Juan dela Cruz\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Juan_dela_Cruz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Juan_dela_Cruz\"}, {\"begin\": 953, \"end\": 964, \"title\": 