, \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Marianne's image in the logo could also be an homage to the rich history of women's participation in the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1405, \"to\": 1524, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1405, \"end\": 1413, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.351479468610666e-37, \"text\": \"Marianne\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Notably, Paris hosted the Games in 1900, marking thefirst time female athletesjoined the international sports competition.\", \"from\": 1526, \"to\": 1648, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1535, \"end\": 1540, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999893134, \"rank\": 1.0626635566462196e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Out of the 997 athletes, 22 women competed across five sports: tennis, sailing, croquet, equestrianism, and golf.\", \"from\": 1649, \"to\": 1762, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The gold medal symbolizes achievement, according to the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1764, \"to\": 1829, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The flame, according to the organizers, symbolizes \\\"the unique energy that drives this mega event, encouraging us to be bold and forge a new way of organising the Games to rise to the challenges we face today.\\\"\", \"from\": 1831, \"to\": 2041, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The organizers said that it was the first time in history the same emblem had been used for both the Olympic Games and the Paralympic Games.\", \"from\": 2043, \"to\": 2183, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The current Paris Olympics logo underwent a transformation from its original conception in 2016 by the Games bid committee.\", \"from\": 2185, \"to\": 23